OL,3,CEver been totally gazeboed? Linguists
OL,4,Cfind 546 'drunkonyms' in English
OL,5,Clanguage
OL,7,FMcIntyre once said during a stand-up
OL,8,Fshow that posh Brits could use any
OL,9,Fword to mean "drunk" in the English
OL,10,Flanguage.
OL,12,FAfter an extensive study recently
OL,13,Fpublished in the , Professors
OL,14,FChristina Sanchez-Stockhammer and
OL,15,FPeter Uhrig found at least 546
OL,16,Fsynonyms for the word "drunk" - dubbed
OL,17,F"drunkonyms" - across the English
OL,18,Flanguage.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/8
