OL,3,CEver been totally gazeboed? Linguists
OL,4,Cfind 546 'drunkonyms' in English
OL,5,Clanguage
OL,7,FThe regular Briton will be familiar
OL,8,Fwith the classics, such as "wasted" or
OL,9,F"hammered". These ol' faithfuls have
OL,10,Fmarked their territory at the top of
OL,11,Fthe nation's favourite drunkonyms list.
OL,13,FBut what about "fried", "toastered",
OL,14,For "sozzled"? Well, they're valid too,
OL,15,Faccording to this study.
OL,17,FThe professors discovered that "drunk"
OL,18,Fmainly occurs in the combinations
OL,19,F"too", "so", or "very" drunk but
OL,20,Funexpectedly, not with the kinds of
OL,21,Fadverb used by McIntyre.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/8
