OL,5,Clanguage
OL,7,FBy contrast, the drunkonyms ending in
OL,8,Fed (for example, "blasted" and
OL,9,F"loaded") most often occur with the
OL,10,Fexpected intensifiers "completely" or
OL,11,F"totally" (like, "completely loaded").
OL,13,FAs expected, the combination of "be"
OL,14,Fplus the intensifying adverb and the
OL,15,Fword ending in -ed is commonly used to
OL,16,Frefer to drunkenness, but not often
OL,17,Fenough to explain how language users
OL,18,Funderstand new drunkonyms, they
OL,19,Fthought.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/8
