OL,7,FThe linguists therefore provided an
OL,8,Fadditional explanation: by the time
OL,9,FEnglish native speakers reach
OL,10,Fadulthood, they have most likely
OL,11,Fexperienced so many different words
OL,12,Fending in -ed meaning "drunk" that it
OL,13,Fallows them to interpret words with
OL,14,Funknown meaning ending in -ed (such as
OL,15,F"cabbaged") as "drunk" in many
OL,16,Fcontexts.
OL,18,FThis is how those 546 drunkonyms are
OL,19,Fexplained.
